message.content:
1. The percentage of patients achieving the MCII for both pain and function at 18 months was 100% for HA1.
2. The percentage of patients achieving the MCII for both pain and function at 18 months was 80% for HA3.
3. The percentage of patients achieving the MCII for both pain and function at 18 months was 60% for HA2.
4. The percentage of patients achieving the MCII for both pain and function at 18 months was 60% for PRP.
5. In the control group, all patients returned to pre-arthroscopy levels.
